race.comment: KNEE DEEP (5) ran a strong race on debut at Geelong, finishing fourth in a bunched finish. The pace wasn't slow there and the ground was heavy so it should be a decent reference. By Dundeel, he should relish the rise to 1600m here and with natural improvement he can get the job done. SIAM EMERALD (3) presents third up. The fresh run at Echuca was good before a sound effort at Ballarat when drawing wide, beaten under a length. Sets up nicely from the ideal gate here and will take catching. BORN SURVIVOR (1) is going well, finishing third in his past three starts, beaten again at $1.35 last start at Wodonga. Not the most reliable but he'll break through eventually and should be a much bigger price this time. DUNTULM LASS (10) was good over this trip at Cranbourne last time out and gets in with just 52kg for the 4kg claiming apprentice. DENY ENTRY (4) is a Fiorente gelding on debut who can run well at a suitable trip.
